# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We need to get the connected component and then identify the border cells of the connected component.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- Run BFS two times
- First BFS : Get all the cells which have the same color as the [row, col] given. This will be the connected component of interest
- Second BFS : Identify which cells from the first BFS are on the border of the connected component. If the color of the child is different than parent, it means parent is a border cell. Similarly, if the parent itself is on the border of the grid, it is a border cell. Change the color of these border cells

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(r*c)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(r*c)


# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> colorBorder(vector<vector<int>>& grid, int row, int col, int color) {
        int r = grid.size();
        int c = grid[0].size();
        queue<pair<int, int>> q;
        queue<pair<int, int>> v;
        vector<vector<bool>> vis(r, vector<bool>(c, false));
        vector<vector<int>> move{{0, 1}, {0, -1}, {-1, 0}, {1, 0}};

        q.push(make_pair(row, col));
        int og = grid[row][col];
        while(!q.empty()){
            auto node = q.front();
            q.pop();
            v.push(node);
            vis[node.first][node.second] = true;
            for(auto mv : move){
                int rn = mv[0] + node.first;
                int rc = mv[1] + node.second;

                if(rn < 0 || rc < 0 || rn>= r || rc>= c)
                    continue;

                if(vis[rn][rc])
                    continue;

                vis[rn][rc] = true;

                if(grid[rn][rc]== og)
                    q.push(make_pair(rn, rc));

            }
        }

        vis.clear();
        vis.resize(r, vector<bool>(c, false));
        while(!v.empty()){
            auto node = v.front();
            v.pop();

            vis[node.first][node.second] = true;
            if(node.first == 0 || node.second == 0 || node.first == r -1 || node.second == c-1){
                grid[node.first][node.second] = color;
                continue;
            }

            bool border = false;
            for(auto mv : move){
                int rn = mv[0] + node.first;
                int rc = mv[1] + node.second;

                if(rn < 0 || rc < 0 || rn>= r || rc>= c)
                    continue;

                if(vis[rn][rc])
                    continue;

                if(grid[rn][rc] != og){
                    border = true;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if(border){
                grid[node.first][node.second] = color;
            }

        }
        return grid;
    }
};
```

