solutions.content:
Logic is an application of *Flood Fill* algorithm. Here, there are two additional conditions to be checked: 

1. bordering cell of the input grid is always a border of the connected component, hence change the color to ncolor. 
2. current cell bordering a cell (in the four direction) with a different color is also a border of the connected component. 

```
class Solution {
    public int[][] colorBorder(int[][] grid, int r, int c, int color) {
        dfs(grid,r,c,color,grid[r][c],new boolean[grid.length][grid[0].length]);
        return grid;
    }

    public void dfs(int[][] grid, int r, int c, int ncolor, int ocolor, boolean[][] visited){

        visited[r][c]=true;

		//1. grid bordering cell is always a border of the connected component
        if( r==grid.length-1 || r==0 || c==0 || c==grid[0].length-1 )
                grid[r][c]=ncolor;

		//2. if the next cell in the four directions is not of the same color, then the current cell is on border of the connected component
        if(r+1<grid.length && !visited[r+1][c]){
            if(grid[r+1][c]==ocolor)
                dfs(grid,r+1,c,ncolor,ocolor,visited);
            else
                grid[r][c]=ncolor;
        }

		if(r-1>=0 && !visited[r-1][c]){
            if(grid[r-1][c]==ocolor)
                dfs(grid,r-1,c,ncolor,ocolor,visited);
            else
                grid[r][c]=ncolor;
        }

        if(c+1<grid[0].length && !visited[r][c+1]){
            if(grid[r][c+1]==ocolor)
                dfs(grid,r,c+1,ncolor,ocolor,visited);  
            else
                grid[r][c]=ncolor;
        }

        if(c-1>=0 && !visited[r][c-1]){
            if(grid[r][c-1]==ocolor)
                dfs(grid,r,c-1,ncolor,ocolor,visited);
            else
                grid[r][c]=ncolor;
        }      
    }
}
```

