```
class Solution {
    public String minInteger(String num, int k) {
        int n = num.length();
        int[] nums = new int[n];
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) nums[i] = Character.getNumericValue(num.charAt(i));
        helper(nums, k);
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            sb.append(nums[i] + "");
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }

    private void helper(int[] nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.length;
        for(int i = 0; i < n && k > 0; i++) {
            int index = i;
            for(int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                if(k < j - i) break;
                if(nums[j] < nums[index]) {
                    index = j;
                }
            }
            for(int j = index; j > i; j--) {
                swap(nums, j, j - 1);
            }
            k -= (index - i);
        }
    }

    private void swap(int[] arr, int a, int b) {
        int tmp = arr[a];
        arr[a] = arr[b];
        arr[b] = tmp;
    }
}
```

The essence lies within the helper function. The idea is to get the smallest digit to the front as best as it could (withing k_curr steps).

