// The solution is base on:
// 1) position queue for each digit
// 2) The entries that removed before the first psition for each digit
// 3) The next digit to add to the return string is the lowest digit which the position minus removed entries not greater than k;
// 4) Update return string; ( time n)
// 5) Update removed entries for each digit; (time 10xn)
// 6) calculate the removed entries for the entry that moved to queue front (for the digit that added to return string); (time nx10)
//  Return to (3)
// Time complexity ~n*22 which is O(n)
