For num[i], if it hasn't been shifted, then just find the minimum digit num[j] that j > i, and num[j] is also not been shifted, and the number of swaps for num[j] to be shifted to i-th index = j - i - digits_shift(i, j) <= k.

If such num[j] exists, num[j] will be shifted to i-th index, otherwise num[i] will be kept.

To count digits_shift between [i, j], since we modify the description that if num[t] has been shifted, Segment Tree is a good data structure to qurry the statistic information of [i, j].

Time: O(NlogN)
Space: O(N)
