solutions.content:
* To make num string sorted, the maximal numer of swaps is n*(n-1)/2. If k is >= this number,  the sorted one could just be returned. (This helps to pass some test cases with TLE).
* getNext() tries to find the smallest character within range k to replace the current character. If it was not found (or the smaller ones are all out of k range), it means the current one is the best one (we don't need to do any swap), we just go to the next position.
* If the smallest one was found, we shift the substring (idx, replacement-idx) one element back, and replace the current one with the smallest one. 
```
class Solution {
public:
    string minInteger(string num, int k) {
        int n = num.size();
        if(k> n*n/2) {
            sort(num.begin(), num.end());
            return num;
        }
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            getNext(num, i, k);
        }
        return num;
    }
    void getNext(string& num, int idx, int& k) {
        int replacement = idx;
        for(char c='0'; c<num[idx]; c++) {
            size_t pos = num.find(c, idx+1);
            if(pos-idx<=k) {
                replacement = pos;
                break;
            }
        }
        if(replacement==idx) return;
        char c = num[replacement];
        for(int i=replacement; i>idx; i--) num[i] = num[i-1];
        num[idx] = c;
        k-=(replacement-idx);  
    }
};

```

