solutions.content:
In the given problem max string length is 30000 and max number of swaps is 10^9.
Therefore it is understood that any k more than n*(n+1)/2 will give the sorted array.
The next step is to find the minimum element and place it in the front under the limit of permissible swaps. Next we count the number of swaps remaining and find the next smallest element and bring it to the second place and so on. If at any point we have a sorted array, we break.
```
string minInteger(string num, int k) {
        int n = num.length();
        string num2 = num;
        sort(num2.begin(),num2.end());
        if(k>(n*(n+1))/2)
        {
            return num2;
        }
        int posi = -1;
        int mini = 10;
        int done = 0;
        while(k>0)
        {
            mini = 10;
            for(int i=done;i<n && i<=done+k;i++)
            {
                if(mini>(num[i]-'0'))
                {
                    posi = i;
                    mini = num[i]-'0';
                }
            }
            for(int i=posi;i>done;i--)
            {
                swap(num[i],num[i-1]);
                k--;
            }
            done++;
            if(num==num2)
                return num2;
        }
        return num;
    }
