Below are the observation.
- If K is too large we can directly return the sorted string.
- Otherwise at each position find the smallest character on right side within K reach and replace current character with it and also move all right side neighbours to right by one position. Reduce K by the distance we got the small character.

```
class Solution {
public:
    string minInteger(string num, int k) {
        int n = num.size();

		/*If K is too large, sort and return*/
        if(k>=n*(n-1)/2){
            sort(num.begin(), num.end());
            return num;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n && k>0;i++){
            char mn = num[i];
            int index=i;
            int tk=k;

			//for the character at index i , find the smallest character with at most K distance
            for(int j= i+1;j<n && tk>0;j++){
                if(mn>num[j]){
				    // save character and index for the swap
                    mn=num[j];
                    index=j;
                }
                tk--;
            }
			// Move all characters from i to min_char_index to the right to make space for the smallest character
            for(int j=index;j>i;j--){
                num[j]=num[j-1];
            }

			//replace current character with minimum char
            num[i]=mn;

			//reduce K
            k-=(index-i);
        }
        return num;
    }
};
```

