solutions.content:
* Here we know that minimum answer can be `1` and maximum can be `10 ^ 7`(mentioned in problem statement).

* We will perform binary search to find the best integer `i` such that:
    - Initially `sum = 0`.
    - for each index `j` in range `0` to `n-1`, `sum = sum + ceil(dist[j] / i)`
    - for `n-1` index, `sum = sum + dist[n-1]/i`. Because the time taken by last train need not be converted into Integer.

```java
class Solution {
    public int minSpeedOnTime(int[] dist, double hour) {
        int n = dist.length;
        int min = 1, max = 10000000;
        int ans = -1;
        while(min <= max){
            int mid = (max + min)/2;
            double sum = 0;
            for(int i = 0; i<n-1; ++i){
                sum += Math.ceil( ( (double) dist[i]) /mid);
            }
            sum = sum + ( ( (double) dist[n-1]) /mid);
            if(sum > hour){
                min = mid+1;
            }else{
                ans = mid;
                max = mid-1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```

