# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Like solving the binary search problem
[875. Koko Eating Bananas
](https://leetcode.com/problems/koko-eating-bananas/solutions/3685871/w-explanation-easy-binary-search-c-solution/)
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
![1870. Minimum Speed to Arrive on Time.png](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/5dd3b273-9ec3-4903-8b0f-ce0c00693205_1690339084.9423194.png)

It is important to know that the function time(speed) is a monotonic (decreasing) function. That is the reason why the binary search can be applied.

To make the binary search efficient, it is suggested to choose the possible smallest searching range. It can derived as follows
$$
hour\geq time(speed) \\
=\sum_{i=0}^{n-2}ceil(\frac{dist[i]}{speed})+\frac{d[n-1]}{speed}\\
\geq (n-1)+\frac{d[n-1]}{speed} , if\ speed \geq max_{i=0,\cdots,n-2} (dist[i])
$$
It implies that
$$
speed\geq \frac{dist[n-1]}{hour-n-1}
$$
So we can choose the initial value for right
```
right=1+max(*max_element(dist.begin(), dist.end()), int(dist[n-1]/(hour-n+1)))
```

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(n \log (m))$$
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$O(1)$
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int n;
    double time(vector<int>& dist, int speed){
        double sum=0;
        for(int i=0; i<n-1; i++)
            sum+=(dist[i]+speed-1)/speed;//ceiling function
        sum+=(double)dist[n-1]/speed;// last one just normal division
        cout<<"speed="<<speed<<",time="<<sum<<endl;
        return sum;
    }
    int minSpeedOnTime(vector<int>& dist, double hour) {
        n=dist.size();

        if (hour<=n-1) return -1;
        long long left=1;
        int right=1+max(*max_element(dist.begin(), dist.end()), int(dist[n-1]/(hour-n+1)));
    //    cout<<right<<endl;
        int speed;
        while(left<=right)
        {
            int mid=left+(right-left)/2;
            if (time(dist, mid)<=hour){
                speed=mid;
                right=mid-1;
            } 
            else left=mid+1;
        }
        return speed;
    }
};
```
