solutions.content:
**Idea:**
* We can try all possible speeds, from 1 to 10^7, to see which one will work. 
* This would be linear search, but we can do binary search since the speed range is sorted
* Find total time (T) for the journey to complete at the given speed, rounding up the time at each stop
* If T > hour, then increase speed
* Else, record this working speed, and decrease it to continue finding a slower speed
>**T/S:** O(n lg M)/O(1), where n = size(distances), M = max speed possible
>In this case M = 10^7, so time complexity is O(n)
```
public int minSpeedOnTime(int[] dist, double hour) {
	var minSpeed = -1;
	var high = (int) 1e7; // top speed allowed

	for (var low = 1; low <= high;) {
		var time = 0d;
		var mid = low + (high - low) / 2;
		var midDouble = (double) mid;

		for (var distance : dist)
			time = Math.ceil(time) + distance / midDouble;

		if (time > hour) {
			low = mid + 1; // too slow, go faster
		} else {
			minSpeed = mid; // record this speed
			high = mid - 1; // this speed works, try going slower
		}
	}

	return minSpeed;
}
