int minSpeedOnTime(vector<int>& dist, double hour) {
        /*
        TIME: O(N*logM) where N is size of input array (number of train rides) and M is maximum between dist of last train ride
        multiplied by 100 and largest element in array
        SPACE: O(1)

        STEP 1: Establish upper and lower bounds of Binary Search:

        But what is the upper bound? Limiting factor is the last train ride.
        For the example above let's say we finished the first 2 train rides as fast as we could and spent 2 hours.
        The smallest hour requirement, that has 2 decimal points, and still makes it possible for us to arrive on time
        is 2.01. This means we have the ride the last train ride in .01 hour. 
        How fast must we travel to get a .01 time? 
        .01 is essentially 1 percent or 1/100 so we must 100x faster than given distance. 
        In example, distance was 3, so we must travel 300 kilometers per hour -> 3/300 = .01 to arrive on time.

        -Thus, upper bound for LAST train ride is last element in input array (dist of last train ride) multipled by 100
        BUT, upper bound for ENTIRE array needs to also consider ALL distances so upper bound is maximum between 
        largest element in array and distance of last train ride multiplied by 100.
        -Lower bound is 1 which is the slowest we could go since answer must be a positive integer

        STEP 2: After getting the mid value = (left + right)/2, iterate through every element in input array and divide
        by mid using ceiling division for all elements EXCEPT the last one. Get the sum of the quotient for every element. 
        What are we doing?
        We are essentially computing the time it takes to travel by dividing the distance of every train ride by the kilometers
        per hour. Use ceiling division because we must wait until the next hour for the train to depart. On the last train ride
        we do not wait for another train ride to depart so must calculate if we arrived at the destination on time. 

        STEP 3: If time we summed up is less than or equal to hour, we made it on time! Check to see if we can travel slower
        and still make it on time (right = mid-1).
        Else, we did not make it on time and must go faster (left=mid+1)

        Repeat STEPS 2-3 until binary search exits, return left pointer which is the slowest speed that still allows us to
        complete the journey on time
        */

        int N=dist.size();                                          // number of required train rides
        int furthest_ride=*max_element(dist.begin(), dist.end());   // furthest train ride (max element in input array)
        int l=1, r=max(furthest_ride, dist[N-1]*100), m;            // binary search variables
        double time=0;                                              // time it takes to complete journey if we travel at m speed

        /*
        Edge case: impossible to reach destination on time because each train ride, except that last ride, takes a least 1 hour
        So N-1, where N is the total number of train rides must be less than hour to spare time for the last train ride
        Example: [1, 2, 3], hour = 2
        There are 3 rides, N=3. The first 2 rides take at least 1 hour each which brings time spent to 2.
        2 is >= hour so impossible to complete ride because we still need to get on the 3rd train ride
        */
        if( N-1>=hour)
            return -1;

        while( l<=r)
        {
            m = (l+r)/2;
            time=0;

            // Compute time it takes to complete journey, traveling at m kilometers per hour
            for(int i=0; i<N; ++i)
            {
                time = ceil(time);  // round up for every train ride except on the last train ride
                time += (double)dist[i]/m;
            }
            // If we arrived exactly on time cannot go any slower and still make it on time, so return speed
            if( time == hour)
                return m;
            // If we made faster than time limit, try to find slower speed
            if( time < hour)
                r = m-1;
            // Else we need to travel faster to make it on time
            else
                l = m+1;
        }
        return l;
    }
