Python3 Solution of the problem with Binary Search Approach.

I am still wondering if there is a better way to identify that the most optimal approach to solving a given problem is just going brute force. By brute force, I mean trying out all possible speeds (even if in binary search manner). Suggestions would be very much welcome!

Time Complexity: O(10e7 * n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

```
import math

class Solution:

    @staticmethod
    def _is_on_time(s, dist, hour):
        """
        Calculates if for a given speed, it is possible to reach withinh the given time
        """
        # This is the fastest method that I could find.
        # Credits: https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-speed-to-arrive-on-time/discuss/1224638/Clean-Python-3-binary-search
        # Original method vs New Method led to a 50% reduction in run time!
        return sum(math.ceil(d / s) for d in dist[:-1]) + dist[-1] / s <= hour

    def _find_optimal_speed(self,dist, min_speed, max_speed, hour):
        # Could be better handled by having this check before this function was called
        if min_speed > max_speed:
            return float('inf')
        if min_speed == max_speed:
            if self._is_on_time(min_speed, dist, hour):
                return min_speed
            return float('inf')

        # The below code can be represented in the following steps:-\
        # 1. Find the mid value between min_speed and max_speed
        # 2. Check if the mid value speed allows us to reach the destination within the given time
        # 3. If yes, then check for values between min_speed and mid-1
                # THIS IS IMPORTANT CONDITION
        # 4. If no, then check for values betweeen mid+1, max_speed
        #       # THIS IS IMPORTANT CONDITION
        mid = int((min_speed + max_speed)/2)
        if self._is_on_time(mid, dist, hour):
            return min(self._find_optimal_speed(dist, min_speed, mid-1, hour), mid)
        else:
            return self._find_optimal_speed(dist, mid+1, max_speed, hour)

    def minSpeedOnTime(self, dist: List[int], hour: float) -> int:
        min_speed = 1  # lowest integer speed possible     
        max_speed = 10000000 # highest integer speed possible (given in the problem description itself)
        optimal_speed = self._find_optimal_speed(dist, min_speed, max_speed, hour)

        # To handle the case when the result is infinity, which implies that we failed to find
        # any solution
        # Suggestions are welcome! :) 
        if optimal_speed > max_speed:
            return -1
        return optimal_speed

```

