class Solution
{
    public:
       LOGIC

    KARNA KYA HAIN❓
    1. Main ek employee hu mujhe office pahuchna hain "hour" mein .
    2. Office pahuchne ke liye mujhe "n" trains in sequential order leni hain.
    3. "dist" array diya hain jo har train kitna distance chalti hain wo batata
    hain.
    4. Ab every train will depart at "integer hour" matlab❓0.33 ke bajaye vo
    1.00 per depart karegi .
    5. Ab aisi kya min speed ho train ki , ki ham hours mein pahuch jaye.
    6. Hame bahut jaldi bhi nahin pahuchna just 1 min pehle bhi pahuch jayu
    hours se to it is success.

    INTUITION & APPROACH
    1. This is a variant of "BS ON ANSWERS PATTERN".
    2. How❓
    - Because we know ki jo bhi speed hogi wo "0" to "1e7" ke beech mein
     ho sakti hain. 1e7 to ques mein bhi mentioned hain.
    - So the answer is lying in the above range we only have to search in halves
    3. "low=0","high=1e7"
    4. har mid ke liye ham time nikalenge har train ka.
    5. Agar no of hours se kam le kisi speed ke liye to it can be one of 
    the answer.
    6. Ham speed aur kam karlenge ("high=mid-1")because we have to find
     the "minimum positive integer".
    7. Agar speed jyada chahiye to "low=mid+1"
    8. Is chiz ka dhyan rakhna hain ki train hamesha "integer hour" per depart
    hogi magar last ke liye integer hour calc karne ki jarurat nahin.
    9. Why❓-> Ab agar ek baar final station per pahuch gaye to ham kyo wait
    karenge train ke departure ka.
    10. "ceil","float" ka dhyan rakhna padega.

//===============================================================================================================================================
        double findTime(vector<int> &dist, int speed)
        {
            double totalTime = 0.0;
            //total time required for a specific speed
            for (int i = 0; i < dist.size() - 1; i++)
            {
                int distance = dist[i];
               double time = distance*1.0/speed;
               //Calculating time for each distance
                totalTime += ceil(time);
                //Rounding off to integer because train can depart
                //at integer hours only
            }
            totalTime += dist[dist.size() - 1] *1.0/speed;
            //Last distance cover karne ke baad employee dosen't
            //have to wait.
            return totalTime;
        }
    int minSpeedOnTime(vector<int> &dist, double hour)
    {
        int low = 0;
        int high = 1e7;
        //ans will lie between low and high
        int ans = -1;
        while (low <= high)
        {
            int mid = (low + high) / 2;
        //mid speed
            if (findTime(dist, mid) <= hour)
            {
                ans = mid;
                high = mid - 1;
                //Found one optimal answer now have to find more
                //optimal answer
            }
            else
                low = mid + 1;
                //Speed required will be more
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```
