# Complexity
- Time complexity:

1. The helper function iterates through the dist vector, which has a size of n, to calculate the time taken for each segment. This takes O(n) time.
2. The minSpeedOnTime function uses binary search to find the minimum speed required. The binary search has a time complexity of O(log S), where S is the search space. Here, the search space is from 1 to 1e7 (10^7). Therefore, the binary search takes O(log 1e7) ≈ O(23) ≈ O(1) time.
Overall, the time complexity of the code is dominated by the O(n) time complexity of the helper function.

- Space complexity:

1. The helper function uses a constant amount of extra space, regardless of the size of the input vector dist. It creates a few variables, but they do not depend on the size of the input. Therefore, the space complexity of the helper function is O(1).
2. The minSpeedOnTime function also uses a constant amount of extra space for variables like l, r, and speed, which do not depend on the size of the input. Therefore, the space complexity of the minSpeedOnTime function is also O(1).

