# Intuition
The goal is to find the minimum speed needed to complete a distance within a specified time. So we use Binary Search.
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
Steps:

- We calculate the time taken to cover the entire distance at the middle speed (mid) in each iteration.
- If the calculated time exceeds the given time limit, we narrow the search range to the upper half (low = mid + 1).
- If the calculated time is within the time limit, we narrow the search range to the lower half (high = mid).
- We continue the binary search until low becomes greater than or equal to high.
