# Intuition
We have to find the min speed of the train and it is given in the question that ans will lie in the range between 1- 10^7.
so for this range we can not use linear approach to find ans. therefore we will be using binary search to  find the min index that will give us the minspeed.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
we will be using binary search for the index in the range between 1 to 10^7.
for this range we will calculate the mid value.
for this mid value we  will calculate the total time that is being taken by the train.


---

To calculate the time taken by train, 
we will iterate through dist array, and then calculate the time that is required at that particular index.
if the iterator (i) will reach the last index than simply we will add the time in a sum variable.
otherwise we have to first find the ceil value and then add that value to the sum variable.

and simply return if the calculated sum<=hour(given).
if this condition is true than it indicates that the mid point can be the ans. 
else we have to search in the right side of mid.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(nlogk)  n ->length of dis[] , k-> the binary search space.
