# Intuition
WHEN WE HAVE QUESTIONS WHERE RANGE OF ANSWER IS FIXED{HERE SPEED}.
AND WE WANT MINIMUM OR MAXIMUM WITH CONDITION. AND THE CONSTRAINTS GENERALLY ARE ~1E5 . THEN WE CAN THINK OF APPLYING BINARY SEARCH ON ANSWERS.

# Approach
speed = dis / time
time =dis/speed
we are given distance , we want select min speed .
Such that summation of all dis/(speed(selected)) is less than given variable hour 
We are catching train in integer hours till the last train . 
We can take double value of dis/(speed(selected))last train as per question .

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(NLOG(1E10)) --> ~ O(N*(34)).

- Space complexity:
 O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool check(double mid,int n , vector<int>&dist,double hour){
        double total_time=0;
        for(int i=0;i<n-1;i++){
            total_time+=ceil(dist[i]/mid);
        }
        if(total_time>=hour)return 0;
        total_time+=(dist[n-1]/mid);
        return total_time<=hour;
    }
    int minSpeedOnTime(vector<int>& dist, double hour) {
        // binary search on speed . and speed will be integer given.
        int n=dist.size();
        long int low=1,high=1e10;
        while(low<=high){
            double mid=low+(high-low)/2;
            if(check(mid,n,dist,hour)){
                high=mid-1;
            }
            else low=mid+1;
        }
        bool final_check=check(low,n,dist,hour);
        if(!final_check)return -1;
        return low;
    }
};

```

